## Component Pattern

Always use functional components with Mantine:

```typescript
import { Group, Stack, Text, Button } from '@mantine/core';

interface MyComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onAction: (id: number) => void;
  optional?: string;
}

export const MyComponent: React.FC<MyComponentProps> = ({ title, onAction, optional }) => {
  const [state, setState] = React.useState<string>('');

  const handleClick = React.useCallback(() => {
    onAction(123);
  }, [onAction]);

  return (
    <Stack gap="sm" p="md">
      <Text fw={600} fz="lg">{title}</Text>
      {optional && <Text fz="sm" c="dimmed">{optional}</Text>}
      <Button onClick={handleClick}>Action</Button>
    </Stack>
  );
};
```

## Styling

Use Mantine style props and the `style` prop:

```typescript
import { Box, Group } from '@mantine/core';

// ✅ Mantine style props for common CSS
<Box p="md" bg="gray.1" style={{ borderRadius: 8 }}>
  <Group gap="sm">...</Group>
</Box>
```

Only use Emotion `styled` when clearly required — custom breakpoints or complex CSS:

```typescript
import styled from '@emotion/styled';
import { media } from '../Styles';

// ✅ Emotion for custom breakpoints (don't match Mantine's built-in ones)
const ResponsiveWrapper = styled.div`
  display: block;
  ${media.mobile`
    display: none;
  `}
`;
```

**Do NOT:**
- Create `styled` wrappers for things Mantine handles (padding, margins, colors, flex layout)
- Wrap Mantine components with `styled()` — it breaks polymorphic props
- Import from `@mui/material` or `@mui/icons-material`

Use the responsive media helpers from `src/client/ui/Styles.ts`:
- `media.mobile` - Screens < 840px
- `media.mobilePortrait` - Screens < 600px
- `media.mobileLandscape` - Screens 600-839px
- `media.web` - Screens >= 600px
- `media.largeDevice` - Screens >= 1400px

## Legacy Patterns (Do NOT Copy)

- `import styled from '@emotion/styled'` with simple layout wrappers
- `import { Button, Box } from '@mui/material'` (MUI imports)
- Custom `VCenterRow`, `Flex` from `GlobalStyles.ts` — use Mantine `Group` / `Flex`
- `PageContentContainer` — deleted, use `ScrollArea`
- Inline style objects for margins/padding — use Mantine style props

When modifying a file with legacy patterns, **rewrite from scratch using Mantine** rather
than patching old code.

## Mantine Reference

- **Theme**: `src/client/ui/theme/mantineTheme.ts` — custom colors (`primary`, `neutral`,
  `action`, `income`), dark mode via virtualColor
- **Font sizes**: Smaller than Mantine defaults (xs=10, sm=12, md=14, lg=16, xl=18).
  Use `md` for normal UI text, `sm` for dense data tables, `xs` for minor labels.
- **Layout**: `BookkeeperPage.tsx` — `AppShell` + `Container` (no card wrapper)
- **Icons**: Use `<Icons.Name />` or `<RenderIcon icon="Name" />` from
  `src/client/ui/icons/Icons.tsx`. Add new icons by importing from `lucide-react`.

## API Calls

Use the `apiConnect` singleton from `client/data/ApiConnect`:

```typescript
import apiConnect from 'client/data/ApiConnect';

const loadData = async () => {
  const expenses = await apiConnect.getExpensesForMonth(year, month);
  setExpenses(expenses);
};
```

## Async Data Loading

Use the custom hooks from `src/client/ui/hooks/`:

```typescript
import { useAsyncData } from './hooks/useAsyncData';

export const MyComponent: React.FC<Props> = ({ id }) => {
  const dataState = useAsyncData(
    () => apiConnect.getItem(id),
    id !== undefined,
    id,
  );

  switch (dataState.type) {
    case 'loaded':
      return <DisplayData data={dataState.value} />;
    case 'error':
      return <ErrorView error={dataState.error} />;
    default:
      return <LoadingSpinner />;
  }
};
```

## State Management

**Zustand** (preferred for new code):

```typescript
import { create } from 'zustand';

interface MyStore {
  items: Item[];
  addItem: (item: Item) => void;
  removeItem: (id: number) => void;
}

export const useMyStore = create<MyStore>((set) => ({
  items: [],
  addItem: (item) => set((state) => ({ items: [...state.items, item] })),
  removeItem: (id) => set((state) => ({
    items: state.items.filter(i => i.id !== id)
  })),
}));
```

**Bacon.js** (legacy — migrate to Zustand when touching these files):

```typescript
import { connect } from '../component/BaconConnect';
import { userDataE, UserDataProps } from 'client/data/Categories';

const MyComponent: React.FC<MyProps> = ({ userData }) => {
  return <div>{userData.categories.map(/* ... */)}</div>;
};

export default connect(userDataE.map(userData => ({ userData })))(MyComponent);
```

## Money Display and Input

Use the Money utility from shared:

```typescript
import { Money } from 'shared/util';

<span>{Money.from(expense.sum).format()}</span>

const amount = Money.from(inputValue);
```

## Date Handling

Use Luxon for date manipulation:

```typescript
import { DateTime } from 'luxon';
import { toISODate, toDateTime } from 'shared/time';

const today = DateTime.now();
const formatted = toISODate(today); // "2024-01-15"
const date = toDateTime('2024-01-15');
date.toFormat('d.M.yyyy'); // "15.1.2024"
```

## Import Paths

Use configured path aliases:

```typescript
import { SomeType } from 'shared/types';
import { Money } from 'shared/util';
import { apiConnect } from 'client/data/ApiConnect';
import { logger } from 'client/Logger';
```

## Dialog Pattern

Use the `UserPrompts` helper from `src/client/ui/dialog/DialogState.ts`:

```typescript
import { UserPrompts } from './dialog/DialogState';

const confirmed = await UserPrompts.confirm('Confirm Delete', 'Are you sure?');
const newName = await UserPrompts.promptText('Rename', 'Enter new name:', currentName);
```

## File Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `ExpenseTable.tsx`, `CategoryPicker.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (e.g., `useAsyncData.ts`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `ClientUtil.ts`)
- Constants/Types: PascalCase (e.g., `Colors.ts`, `Types.ts`)

## Type Checking

After changes, verify with `bun lint-tsc`. Common issues:
- `any` types — prefer proper types or `unknown` for error handling
- Bacon.js Property vs EventStream type mismatches
- Handling `unknown` error types (use `instanceof Error` checks)

## Adding New Features

1. Create component files in the appropriate `ui/` subdirectory
2. Define any new types in `shared/types/` or `shared/expense/`
3. Add API methods to `client/data/ApiConnect.ts` if needed
4. Create custom hooks in `ui/hooks/` for reusable logic
5. Export components appropriately (named exports preferred)
6. Run `bun lint-tsc` to verify no type errors were introduced
